Title: Block Editor

See also: U006

Main Behavior:

1. User types the command to launch the block editor (e.g., 10 LIST to jump directly to block 10; just EDIT to re-edit the last block).
2. User sees the cursor appear on line 1 of the specified block.  The user may then edit the block contents, or navigate to other blocks.

Exceptional Behavior:

1a. If no block file is currently set for the indicated block, an error is displayed and control returns to the OK prompt.

